	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have been lurking around these forums for a while already, but I just registered for an account to thank Shiru for this great tool.
<br />
<br />In a community that I am part of, there is a small competition going on recently, that you take a classic adventure game, make sprites and mock-up screens of it, as though the game is made by a different developer on another system. It is a coincidence that NESST was released at the same time and so I decided to give it a go.
<br />
<br />This is what I did:
<br /><img src="http://i488.photobucket.com/albums/rr249/gilbot/fcdye.png" alt="Image" />
<br />And, the ROM (with source):
<br /><a href="http://www.mediafire.com/?saqov494ymhbq74" class="postlink">http://www.mediafire.com/?saqov494ymhbq74</a>
<br />
<br />This is also my first "working" Famicom ROM.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=":wink:" title="Wink" /> 
<br />(As I'm not really going to do any more work on it, I think this post does not belong to the Homebrew section or a thread of its own; I just cut in to say thanks.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
